### Test plan (hermetic, deterministic — stub check + seat runners, NO real LLM)
All via injected ResolveCheck/ResolveSeat/Tiers stubs returning canned verdicts; assert against the written manifest (ParseJSON of the run ref).
- AC1 records a GateAttempt with the synthesized verdict: one stage+gate, passing check + 2 go seats -> run succeeds; manifest has one GateAttempt, Status==pass, gate_id "<phase>.r1", seats=[check.0,seatA,seatB] with right verdicts/provider/harness, reviewed_stages binds the output sha. ALSO assert the run with gates serializes manifest_version==3 and round-trips JSON()->ParseJSON intact (opus — defect #5 exercised by a hermetic test, not just smoke).
- AC2 failing check hard-blocks over passing seats: check exits nonzero, 2 go seats, max_rounds=1 -> status NOT pass (rerun->escalated at max_rounds); the failing check recorded `block`; gate did not pass despite unanimous seat go.
- AC3 rerun re-executes stage with feedback + bumps round: round 1 seats block (max_rounds>=2); stub stage runner asserts it received input role gate-feedback containing the blocking required[]; round 2 seats go. Assert two GateAttempts (r1 rerun, r2 pass), a second Stage named "<stage>.r2" with feedback in its Inputs, chain role unchanged.
- AC4 escalate advances tier: gate at tier L3 (single stub seat blocks) max_rounds=1 -> r1 escalated; ladder L3->L2 (two stub go seats) -> r2 at L2 passes. Assert attempt1 Tier==3 status==escalated with escalation_reason, attempt2 Tier==2 status==pass; round monotonic. Plus terminal case: top tier L1 still blocks -> GateEscalationError, partial run valid (run show works, escalated recorded).
- AC5 fail-closed: (a) 2 seats, one Err (errored) -> usable=1 < min(2,2) -> escalated; errored seat recorded `failed`+failure_note, skipped. (b) malformed-envelope seat -> `malfunction`, skipped. (c) threshold: 3 seats, pass_threshold 0.5, 2 go/1 block -> 0.67>=0.5 -> pass; same with pass_threshold 1.0 -> 0.67<1.0 -> rerun/escalated. (d) checks-only gate (no seats), check passes -> pass (no <2 fail-closed).

