### Risks
- Loop complexity (rerun x tier escalation) is the largest surface; bounded by tiers x max_rounds with a monotonic round, isolated in one tested synthesize + drive function.
- Rerun in an evolving worktree re-executes a possibly-mutated tree; non-idempotent stage runners (e.g. implement) could double-apply. Consistent with the etude-xin single-worktree decision; documented, not solved here.
- Tier int vs registry L-tier mismatch (manifest Tier is 0-3; registry L1-L4): L4/inline -> Tier 0. Lossy but valid; escalation uses tier NAMES not the int. Documented.
- Literal "<2 usable" implemented as min(2,expected) to not break a single-seat tier; deviation stated/justified up front.
- Scope fence: gate EXECUTION only. NOT migrating the dev workflow (etude-2pc.2), NOT changing secret/env passthrough (etude-3a2); tier/seat DEFINITIONS come from the etude-2pc.1 registry unchanged.

